This paper discusses the emergence of evolvability and canalization in an evolutionary system, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of an interactive evolutionary system also suggests a focus on robotics and control systems (cs.RO, cs.SY). Finally, the study of evolutionary systems falls under the category of neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE).
